import gc
import copy
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import shapely.geometry
def test_get_indices():
    a = [(i + 100) for i in range(10)]
    lookup = {idx: pos for pos, idx in enumerate(a)}
    lookup['before_fuse'] = a
    result = get_indices([102, 107], lookup, fused_indices=True)
    assert np.array_equal(result, [2, 7])
    result = get_indices([2, 7], lookup, fused_indices=False)
    assert np.array_equal(result, [102, 107])
    lookup[107] = lookup[102]
    result = get_indices([102, 107], lookup, fused_indices=True)
    assert np.array_equal(result, [2, 2])
    result = get_indices([2, 7], lookup, fused_indices=False)
    assert np.array_equal(result, [102, 107])

test_get_indices()

import os
import math
import copy
import pandas as pd
import pytest
from geopandas import testing
from shapely.geometry import Point
from shapely.geometry import LineString
from geopandas import GeoDataFrame
from geopandas import points_from_xy
def test__convert_xy_epsg():
    x = 9.487
    y = 51.32
    result = _convert_xy_epsg(x, y, 4326, 31467)
    expected = 3534023, 5687359
    assert result == pytest.approx(expected)
    result = _convert_xy_epsg(x, y, 4326, 3857)
    expected = 1056088, 6678094
    assert result == pytest.approx(expected)
    x = 3534023
    y = 5687359
    result = _convert_xy_epsg(x, y, 31467, 4326)
    expected = 9.487, 51.32
    assert result == pytest.approx(expected, abs=0.001)
    x = [9.487, 9]
    y = [51.32, 51]
    result_x, result_y = _convert_xy_epsg(x, y, 4326, 31467)
    expected_x, expected_y = [3534023, 3500073], [5687359, 5651645]
    assert result_x == pytest.approx(expected_x)
    assert result_y == pytest.approx(expected_y)

test__convert_xy_epsg()
